### Prerender Router (With Namespace) - JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/packages/embeds/README.md

Prerenders a router instance within a specified namespace, allowing for organized management of multiple Cal.com embeds. This enhances maintainability and prevents potential naming conflicts in complex applications. Similar to the non-namespaced version, it optimizes user engagement by preparing the booking flow in advance.

```javascript
Cal.ns.myNamespace('prerender', {
  calLink: "router?formId=123&ONLY_THOSE_FIELDS_THAT_ARE_REQUIRED_BY_ROUTING_RULES_SHOULD_BE_PRESENT_HERE",
  // Prerender right now works only with "modal", so 'element click' embed is able to reuse this prerendered iframe
  type: "modal"
  // Shows skeleton loader for a Team Event's booking slots page
  pageType: "team.event.booking.slots"
});
```

